    <section id="fs-id2590398" type="problems-exercises" class="problems-exercises"><title>Problems &amp; Exercises</title><exercise id="fs-id1615066" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2097366">    <para id="import-auto-id1369808">(a) By how many percent is the torque of a motor decreased if its permanent magnets lose 5.0% of their strength? (b) How many percent would the current need to be increased to return the torque to original values?</para>
    </problem>
<solution id="fs-id1586533">
    <para id="import-auto-id2883321">(a) <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext> τ</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{" τ"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> decreases by 5.00% if B decreases by 5.00%</para>
