<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1168951439003"><term>motor</term><meaning id="fs-id1168951439006">loop of wire in a magnetic field; when current is passed through the loops, the magnetic field exerts torque on the loops, which rotates a shaft; electrical energy is converted to mechanical work in the process</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1168951431292"><term>meter</term><meaning id="fs-id1168951430590">common application of magnetic torque on a current-carrying loop that is very similar in construction to a motor; by design, the torque is proportional to  <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math> and not  <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>, so the needle deflection is proportional to the current</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
